snippet.textDisplay:
My dad had a Samsung Galaxy Mega. He loved it (he had big hands) until the phone shit the bed after a forced software update and our carrier and the Samsung rep at best buy said they could not put him back to the previous software OS he had and told him he just needs to get a new phone. Now he swears he will never buy another Samsung phone again and he hasn't for the past 7 years.

Similar thing happened with my OG Google Pixel. Android 10 came out and wrecked the battery life, no easy and clean way to go back to Android 9 which forced me to get a new phone, despite my Pixel being in great shape and worked flawlessly for me. Other than the huge chin it was the perfect size phone for me and function. I was actually looking at upgrading to a Pixel 3a, but after that experience and seeing other Pixels were having battery issues with the update - even brand new phones and Google never coming up with an update to fix the phone, I said the same thing. I will now never own a Google Pixel phone despite them always having the features I like most about the phones and pure android experience. Now I'm with a OP7T, really looked hard at Samsung too, but cannot get past the bloatware on the devices ever since having a pure android experience.

Samsung should allow for that and I'm sure their sales would go up higher than they already are. Nobody wan't a Bixby button....
